<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
		================================================================
		IMPORTANT — entitlements are temporarily stripped for Personal Team
		================================================================

		Personal Apple IDs (free tier) can NOT use these two capabilities:
		  - aps-environment              (Push Notifications)
		  - com.apple.developer.associated-domains  (Universal Links)

		Until Xcode shows your paid Apple Developer team in the
		Signing & Capabilities → Team dropdown, both entries below stay
		commented out so the Personal Team can sign the build for
		on-device development.

		WHEN YOUR PAID TEAM APPEARS IN XCODE:
		  1. Open Xcode → click the App target → Signing & Capabilities
		  2. Switch the Team dropdown from "(Personal Team)" to your
		     paid team
		  3. Uncomment the two <key> blocks below (delete the wrapping
		     <!-- and -->)
		  4. In the Signing & Capabilities tab, click "+ Capability"
		     and re-add "Push Notifications" + "Associated Domains"
		  5. Build and run — the provisioning profile error clears

		How to make the paid team show up:
		  - Xcode → Settings → Accounts → click your Apple ID →
		    click "Download Manual Profiles", or sign out and back in
		  - On developer.apple.com, accept any pending agreement under
		    Account → Agreements (Apple sometimes adds one post-payment)
		  - Wait 24-48h after payment confirmation if neither of the
		    above surfaces the team

		Push notifications + Universal Links code paths in the app are
		guarded so they no-op when entitlements are missing — nothing
		else breaks while these are commented out.
	-->

	<!--
	<key>aps-environment</key>
	<string>development</string>
	<key>com.apple.developer.associated-domains</key>
	<array>
		<string>applinks:edentrack.app</string>
	</array>
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
